Runrar (Recursive Unrar) is an unrar wrapper designed to descend into a
directory tree and unrar all archives found. For example, archived media that
is saved in a hierarchical manner.

It requires that unrar be installed and in the user's path. It has a command
line format as such:

runrar [arg1...arg2]

    -t target_directory
        
        the directory to begin search for archives. defaults to the directory
        in which the command is run. 

    -s save_directory
        
        where the files will be saved after unarchiving.
